entries.journal_entry_description: Boss Nass thinks maybe you can learn how to get past the security on Ultragungan droids from an Ultragungan Militia member.
entries.task00_journal_entry_description: Go to the Ultragungan foot soldier camps and fight the foot soldiers. Maybe one of them will know how to bypass the hardware security on the droids. There are a number of foot soldier camps in the area.
entries.task01_journal_entry_description: Now you're getting somewhere: one of the foot soldiers let slip that the self-destruct security mechanism is bypassed using a password. Now you just need to find that password. Ultragungan droidtechs would be a good place to start.
entries.task01_message_box_text: Now you're getting somewhere: one of the foot soldiers let slip that the self-destruct security mechanism is bypassed using a password. Now you just need to find that password. Ultragungan droidtechs would be a good place to start.
entries.task02_journal_entry_description: Convince Ultragungan droidtechs to reveal the password to their droids.
entries.task03_comm_message_text: It was foolish to dink te droidtechs would reveal anydin', but dey sparkin' a dought. Find da toolkit usin' by da droidtechs, and mesa'll bet wesa find da password.
entries.task04_journal_entry_description: Find a toolkit used by an Ultragungan droidtech. Boss Nass thinks he can get the droid security password from one of the toolkits.
entries.task04_journal_entry_title: Find an Ultragungan Militia Droidtech's Tools
entries.task05_journal_entry_description: Return to Boss Nass, and he'll examine the Ultragungan droidtech's toolkit.
